Maleme

March 43.  After the German Africa corps (DAK) had brought Egypt under its control, the island of Crete is the only British post in the eastern Mediterranean. The OKW (Wehrmacht Supreme Command) decides to conquer Crete, too. The Royal Navy, however, is still very strong.  In a secret action the German have succeeded in gaining a foothold on the island.  But the British are warned ...
The crucial point of this fictitious scenario is the Maleme airfield. Without it there won't be any airborne reinforcements for the Wehrmacht.  

